 <text>
  <front>
   <head>TO LORENZO.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Go, distant shores and brighter conquests seek,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But my affection will your scorn survive!</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">For not from radiant eyes or crimson cheek</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">My fondness I, or you your power derive; —</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Nor sprung the passion from your fancied love;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To me, your smiles no dear delusion caused;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I saw you tower my humble hopes above,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And, ere I loved, I shuddered, trembled, paused.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="sestarima">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But I was formed to prize superior worth,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And felt 't was virtue you, with love, to see;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I hoped a choice so glorious might call forth</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Merit like yours, Lorenzo, e'en in me. —</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Then go, assured that mine's no transient flame,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">For on your worth it feeds, and lives upon your fame.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
